I think I found a bug in DisplayObjectContainer.as

Line 214:

``` as3
public function setChildIndex(child:DisplayObject, index:int):void
{
    var oldIndex:int = getChildIndex(child);
    if (oldIndex == -1) throw new ArgumentError("Not a child of this container");
         mChildren.splice(oldIndex, 1);
         mChildren.splice(index, 0, child);
    }
}
```

If the index is higher than the oldIndex then the object is spliced at the wrong position.

It should probably be something like this:

``` as3
public function setChildIndex(child:DisplayObject, index:int):void
{
    var oldIndex:int = getChildIndex(child);
    if (oldIndex == -1) throw new ArgumentError("Not a child of this container");
         mChildren.splice(oldIndex, 1);
         if(oldIndex < index && index > 0){
             mChildren.splice(index-1, 0, child);
         }
         else{
             mChildren.splice(index, 0, child);
         }
    }
}
```

inner loop currently looks like:

``` actionscript
for (i=vertexID; i<numVertices; ++i)
```

and gives broken results with non zero vertexID input. Propably it should be something like

``` actionscript
for (i=vertexID; i<vertexID+numVertices; ++i)
```

there is some room for performance optimizations (e.g. not using ternary operators but rather "if" etc.)

here is my fixed static/utils implementation

``` actionscript
public static function getBounds(vertexData:VertexData, vertexID:int=0, numVertices:int=-1):Rectangle
{
    if (numVertices < 0 || vertexID + numVertices > vertexData.numVertices)
        numVertices = vertexData.numVertices - vertexID;

    var minX:Number = Number.MAX_VALUE, maxX:Number = -Number.MAX_VALUE;
    var minY:Number = Number.MAX_VALUE, maxY:Number = -Number.MAX_VALUE;
    var offsetX:int = vertexID * VertexData.ELEMENTS_PER_VERTEX + VertexData.POSITION_OFFSET;
    var offestY:int = offsetX + 1;
    for(var i:uint = vertexID, length:uint = numVertices + vertexID; i < length; ++i)
    {
        var x:Number = vertexData.rawData[offsetX];
        var y:Number = vertexData.rawData[offestY];
        offsetX += VertexData.ELEMENTS_PER_VERTEX;
        offestY = offsetX + 1;

        if(minX > x)
            minX = x;
        if(maxX < x)
            maxX = x;
        if(minY > y)
            minY = y;
        if(maxY < y)
            maxY = y;
    }

    return new Rectangle(minX, minY, maxX - minX, maxY - minY);
}
```

